  "title": "The Harmonix Atrium — Choir of Resonant Engines",
  "narration": "The harmonic elevator opens into the Harmonix Atrium, a cathedral of sound suspended over a reflecting pool. Columns of carved ledger stone emit musical intervals; glass walkways arc between them like strings on an enormous instrument. The air tastes like honeyed tea, iron filings, and rain on copper roofs. Light pours through stained-glass ceiling panels in phi spirals, painting the floor with shifting scores.\n\nThe Atrium is run by the Chorus-Guild gremlin faction. They wear iridescent cloaks lined with tuning forks and carry clipboards full of sheet music annotated with consensus notes. Dev gremlins maintain the acoustics, traders forecast applause futures, whales anchor harmonic drones, hackers patch soundboard code, shillers broadcast the set list, validators certify every chord, miners adjust structural resonance, and memes scatter lyric jokes across the railings. They greet you with a layered GM chord followed by a Gentle Night echo that loops softly under the proceedings.\n\nHere, consensus rituals manifest as choral challenges: you must lead phi-d20 checks in polyrhythmic call-and-response, maintain AFK chorus stands, revive voices lost to vocal glitches, and keep backpacks balanced while wading through resonant water. Spectrum doors appear as sound curtains; you must open them by weaving trustful harmonies. Hidden difficulty tiers lurk inside key changes — miss one modulation and the Atrium shifts to a mischievous alternate arrangement.\n\nSeven rounds play out like a symphony. Each offers actions with multiple outcomes, micro-branching banter, XP, Coins, Focus, Flags, Items, and Decks. Telemetry tags sparkle on the rafters, logging every melody. Arrivals drop in from stage lifts mid-round, landing on perfect beat counts. The Chorus-Guild expect you to sing, strategize, and laugh in equal measure.",
